Document: GradientTexture2D
Path: godot/classes/class_gradienttexture2d.rst
Summary: Defines the properties that control the appearance and behavior of a GradientTexture2D resource.

Properties:
* fill (Fill): Controls how the gradient is applied. Default: 0.
* fill_from (Vector2): The starting point for the gradient fill. Default: Vector2(0, 0).
* fill_to (Vector2): The ending point for the gradient fill. Default: Vector2(1, 0).
* gradient (Gradient): The Gradient resource to be used for the texture.
* height (int): The height of the generated texture in pixels. Default: 64.
* repeat (Repeat): Controls how the gradient texture repeats. Default: 0.
* resource_local_to_scene (bool): If true, the resource will be duplicated and its path will be updated when the scene is saved. This overrides the same property from Resource. Default: false.
* use_hdr (bool): If true, the texture will be generated in HDR format (32-bit float colors). Default: false.
* width (int): The width of the generated texture in pixels. Default: 64.
---CHUNK---
Document: GradientTexture2D
Path: godot/classes/class_gradienttexture2d.rst
Summary: Defines enumerations for fill types and repeat modes for GradientTexture2D.

Enumerations:
Fill:
  FILL_LINEAR (0): The colors are linearly interpolated in a straight line.
  FILL_RADIAL (1): The colors are linearly interpolated in a circular pattern.
  FILL_SQUARE (2): The colors are linearly interpolated in a square pattern.
  FILL_CONIC (3): The colors are linearly interpolated in a cone pattern.

Repeat:
  REPEAT_NONE (0): The gradient fill is restricted to the range defined by fill_from to fill_to offsets.
  REPEAT (1): The texture is filled starting from fill_from to fill_to offsets, repeating the same pattern in both directions.
  REPEAT_MIRROR (2): The texture is filled starting from fill_from to fill_to offsets, mirroring the pattern in both directions.
