Document: GradientTexture2D
Path: godot/classes/class_gradienttexture2d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and member variables of the GradientTexture2D class in Godot Engine.

Property: fill
Type: Fill (enum)
Description: The gradient's fill type.
Default: 0

Property: fill_from
Type: Vector2
Description: The initial offset used to fill the texture specified in UV coordinates.
Default: Vector2(0, 0)

Property: fill_to
Type: Vector2
Description: The final offset used to fill the texture specified in UV coordinates.
Default: Vector2(1, 0)

Property: gradient
Type: Gradient
Description: The Gradient used to fill the texture.

Property: height
Type: int
Description: The number of vertical color samples that will be obtained from the Gradient, which also represents the texture's height.
Default: 64

Property: repeat
Type: Repeat (enum)
Description: The gradient's repeat type.
Default: 0

Property: use_hdr
Type: bool
Description: If true, the generated texture will support high dynamic range (Image.FORMAT_RGBAF format). This allows for glow effects to work if Environment.glow_enabled is true. If false, the generated texture will use low dynamic range; overbright colors will be clamped (Image.FORMAT_RGBA8 format).
Default: false

Property: width
Type: int
Description: The number of horizontal color samples that will be obtained from the Gradient, which also represents the texture's width.
Default: 64